Project Report: Project Alpha

Project Alpha is a machine learning initiative focused on real-time anomaly detection for financial transactions.
The primary goal is to reduce fraudulent activity by 90%.
The technology stack includes Python, Kafka for data streaming, and TensorFlow for the ML model.
The project is currently in Phase 2 (Development) and is on track to meet its Q4 deadline.
Key stakeholders include the finance department and the risk management team.
